<scope ilk="blob" lang="PHP" name="ConstraintViolationInterface.php" src="/usr/local/pear/share/pear/PhpDocumentor/vendor/symfony/validator/Symfony/Component/Validator/ConstraintViolationInterface.php"><scope doc="This file is part of the Symfony package.&#10;&#10;(c) Fabien Potencier &lt;fabien@symfony.com&gt;&#10;&#10;For the full copyright and license information, please view the LICENSE&#10;file that was distributed with this source code." ilk="namespace" line="12" name="Symfony\Component\Validator"><scope ilk="interface" line="38" lineend="136" name="ConstraintViolationInterface" signature="ConstraintViolationInterface"><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the violation message.&#10;&#10;@return string The violation message.&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="47" lineend="47" name="getMessage" returns="string" signature="string getMessage()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the raw violation message.&#10;&#10;The raw violation message contains placeholders for the parameters&#10;returned by {@link getMessageParameters}. Typically you'll pass the&#10;message template and parameters to a translation engine.&#10;&#10;@return string The raw violation message.&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="60" lineend="60" name="getMessageTemplate" returns="string" signature="string getMessageTemplate()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the parameters to be inserted into the raw violation message.&#10;&#10;@return array A possibly empty list of parameters indexed by the names&#10;              that appear in the message template.&#10;&#10;@see getMessageTemplate&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="72" lineend="72" name="getMessageParameters" returns="array" signature="array getMessageParameters()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns a number for pluralizing the violation message.&#10;&#10;For example, the message template could have different translation based&#10;on a parameter &quot;choices&quot;:&#10;&#10;&lt;ul&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Please select exactly one entry. (choices=1)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;li&gt;Please select two entries. (choices=2)&lt;/li&gt;&#10;&lt;/ul&gt;&#10;&#10;This method returns the value of the parameter for choosing the right&#10;pluralization form (in this case &quot;choices&quot;).&#10;&#10;@return integer|null The number to use to pluralize of the message." ilk="function" line="90" lineend="90" name="getMessagePluralization" returns="integer" signature="integer getMessagePluralization()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the root element of the validation.&#10;&#10;@return mixed The value that was passed originally to the validator when&#10;              the validation was started. Because the validator traverses&#10;              the object graph, the value at which the violation occurs&#10;              is not necessarily the value that was originally validated.&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="102" lineend="102" name="getRoot" returns="mixed" signature="mixed getRoot()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the property path from the root element to the violation.&#10;&#10;@return string The property path indicates how the validator reached&#10;               the invalid value from the root element. If the root&#10;               element is a &lt;tt&gt;Person&lt;/tt&gt; instance with a property&#10;               &quot;address&quot; that contains an &lt;tt&gt;Address&lt;/tt&gt; instance&#10;               with an invalid property &quot;street&quot;, the generated property&#10;               path is &quot;address.street&quot;. Property access is denoted by&#10;               dots, while array access is denoted by square brackets,&#10;               for example &quot;addresses[1].street&quot;.&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="118" lineend="118" name="getPropertyPath" returns="string" signature="string getPropertyPath()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns the value that caused the violation.&#10;&#10;@return mixed The invalid value that caused the validated constraint to&#10;              fail.&#10;&#10;@api" ilk="function" line="128" lineend="128" name="getInvalidValue" returns="mixed" signature="mixed getInvalidValue()" /><scope attributes="public" doc="Returns a machine-digestible error code for the violation.&#10;&#10;@return mixed The error code." ilk="function" line="135" lineend="135" name="getCode" returns="mixed" signature="mixed getCode()" /></scope></scope></scope>